# Help: KUnit kernel unit testing framework
#
# KUNIT is tristate. KUNIT=y is chosen so tests run during boot via
# KUNIT_AUTORUN_ENABLED. With KUNIT=m, tests only run when the
# module is loaded, which happens late in userspace and misses most
# of the boot sequence.
# See: https://docs.kernel.org/dev-tools/kunit/
CONFIG_KUNIT=y
CONFIG_KUNIT_DEFAULT_ENABLED=y
CONFIG_KUNIT_AUTORUN_ENABLED=y
CONFIG_KUNIT_DEBUGFS=y
